                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#000000"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Nettling Wraiths amd the banshee's are located due east of zone-in, on the far side of the zone. You need to head for the ZO2 and set up camp in that region.<br /><br />Banshee's are undead and may be slowed, but summon. I have never tried to solo one.<br /><br />Wraiths are not undead, and do not summon (except for 'A Wraith' - who summons quite happilly).<br /><br />Nettling Wraiths are snareable, rootable, but not fearable (all are level 55 according to Allakhazam, and from the consistently good XP I received from every kill I would agree with this). <br /><br />Up to level 60 you get the 5 level bonus, but at 61 XP drops dramatically and I would not recommend staying here when you ding 61 (60 XP = a little under 2% normal XP and 4% AAXP per kill).<br /><br />To reach the Wraiths, invis up and head North from the zone-in. on the ZI side of the river only Treants, and spiders will see through invis. Make your way to three-raven-rock that is East and slightly North of zone-in, near to the river. <br /><br />I usually go slightly North of ZI and then head east, along the southern edge of the small plateau that sits in the middle of the Northern area of this side of the river. The three-raven-rock is on the South-East corner of the plateau. When you reach the river be careful of hobgoblins who may also see through invis. As always, keep feign death ready for emergencies.<br /><br />To the East of the Raven rock are two stones on the edge of the drop down to the River. Climb one (invised and Dead Man Floating) and look slightly to your right. You should see a tree on the far bank. This tree is situated between two alligateroids, by keeping your head up for altitude and heading for that tree you should safely cross the river withour agravating them. <br /><br />Once you reach the far side stop, and head NNE towards the plateau that is near-by. Never sit at the base of this plateau or you may agro the level 61 mobs that spawn on top. Continue North-North-East until you pass the plateau and can run along the Northern zone wall to the hedge and Zone out 2 (ZO2 is the gravestone - click to return to PoT).<br /><br />Congratulations you are now at your camp-site. Set up camp at either the Northern wall (West of ZO2 - my favourite spot since roamers can pass fairly close to the Eastern wall) or along the East wall.<br /><br />Pulling.<br /><br />The pulling area is immediately infront of you - you can also pull from a static spawn towards the river but there is terrible pathing and those pulls will probably warp onto you. Visibility is quite good, a flat area with some trees and rocks to be cautious of.<br /><br />An HP buff is much recommended but I seldom bothered and seldom died. I pulled with dooming darkness back to my base, dotting as I went (Splurt and Pyro). When I reached the base I usually threw on another dooming, pulled it along the wall for thirty seconds and then sent in the un-taunting pet (save yourself a Peridot and use the Rogue pet). As long as you reapply dooming darkness in good time, all is golden.<br /><br />No summons, no adds, no fuss.<br /><br />However it doesn't always go to plan. When pulling you will find that one in four snares fails to stick. I used a Green Silken Drape (50pp in the bazaar) for the Affliction Haste II effect, and I could usually run a short way and recast in time to only receive one round of melee damage (600 or so damage usually). Unfortunately these things run faster than SoW (or SoE) so there is no way to avoid taking some damage. You could try feigning after the 1st failure and recasting when it moves away but typically I just tried to re-doom.<br /><br />If dooming fails twice you might still survive. I never lived through three failures though.<br /><br />Steelskin before pulling for safety.<br /><br />Rhys<br /><br /><img src="http://www.clement-evans.co.uk/xatan/xatan-eyes.jpg" border="0"></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
                    </tr>
